%N A392462 a(n) is the minimum diameter of a n-element set of integers for which no nonzero d has more than 3 representations as a difference of elements of the set.
%C A392462 a(n) is the minimum diameter of a 3-Golomb Ruler.
%C A392462 a(3) >= (n^2-2n^{3/2}+n)/3+sqrt(n)-1, by a version of the Erdos-Turan argument for Sidon sets.
%C A392462 a(1) through a(10) computed by Hassenklover (1984).
%C A392462 a(q) <= (q^2-1)/3 - 1, if q is a prime power, proved by Caicedo, Martos and Trujillo (2015).
%C A392462 a(n) ~ n^2/3, proved by Caicedo, Martos and Trujillo (2015).
%C A392462 a(n) >= (n^2 - (2-e)n^{3/2})/3 for some e>0 and sufficiently large n, proved by Balogh, Füredi and Roy (2023).
%C A392462 a(n) >= (n^2 - (1-2^{-14})n^{3/2})/3 for sufficiently large n, proved by Carter, Hunter and O'Bryant (2025).
